I"²<div class="p">Ancestral fire self-fattens on men's hearts,</div>
<div class="p">And strains 'gainst drumlike chests in pride,</div>
<div class="p">Issues from mouths, like flaming darts,</div>
<div class="p">And licks up envy's side.</div>
<p>Â </p>
<div class="p">But rancid liqueur quenches the bold flames,</div>
<div class="p">And sops up virtue's residue,</div>
<div class="p">And notwithstanding one exclaims,</div>
<div class="p">Breaks up the pas de deux.</div>
<p>Â </p>
<div class="p">No more the oily liqueurs burn nor choke</div>
<div class="p">Nor tear eyes with their thick, gray smoke;</div>
<div class="p">And twining rivulets of flames and poke</div>
<div class="p">Nor twine, nor nip, nor soak.</div>
<p>Â </p>
<div class="p">The pitchy waters overrun the state,</div>
<div class="p">And drown in oil, a medicine</div>
<div class="p">By quacks prescribed against the date,</div>
<div class="p">Frail men decocted in sin.</div>
